obj_administrative_notes: This DVD was originally awarded as an AV object and listed as a format "DV" and sent with their 23-24 materials.
obj_partner_admin_notes: The original of this disc has been digitized by Cal Rev.  However, the sound was corrupted.  This copy has full sound. Only a tiny handful of these dics seem to have been created from U-matic and Betacam SP originals.
label: Olympic Torch Relay
obj_significance: In 1996, Huntington Beach was the first stop of the Olympic Torch on its way to Atlanta.  A radio broadcast including organizers and one of two local women chosen to run the torch through the city were featured in this tape.
